article.headline: Montana 35, Cal Poly 23
article.story: MISSOULA, Mont. -- Marc Mariani caught six passes for 200 yards and two touchdowns and Chase Reynolds rushed for 109 yards and scored three times as Montana rallied past Cal Poly 35-23 Saturday. Mariani scored on pass plays of 84 and 68 yards to help the Grizzlies overcome five turnovers and remain undefeated (5-0). Jordan Yocum rushed for 119 yards and scored on a 1-yard run to give the Mustangs (2-3) a 17-7 lead with 1:09 remaining before halftime. Reynolds found the end zone twice in the fourth quarter when Montana scored 21 points to overcome a 17-14 deficit. He added another 44 yards on two receptions, both of which went for touchdowns.
